parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Oil Consumption and Engine Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive oil consumption and engine failure can cause the engine to seize, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. It can also result in costly repairs, replacement of the engine, and loss of vehicle value.
symptoms: The vehicle burns excessive oil
often without warning
leading to engine failure
seizing
or stalling. The oil light may not come on
and there may be no indication of a problem until the engine fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: PCV Valve Failure and Sludge Buildup
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PCV valve can cause sludge buildup, leading to engine failure, seizing, or stalling. It can also result in costly repairs, replacement of the engine, and loss of vehicle value.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience excessive oil consumption
engine stalling
or seizing
and may have a loud clunking or knocking noise. The PCV valve may be clogged
and there may be sludge buildup in the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Low Oil Pressure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine due to low oil pressure can cause the engine to seize, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. It can also result in costly repairs, replacement of the engine, and loss of vehicle value.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience engine stalling or seizing
and the oil light may come on. There may be no indication of a problem until the engine fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without pressing the gas pedal
the accelerator pedal becomes hard to press
the vehicle accelerates while slowing down or coming to a stop
the engine revs into the red zone
the vehicle accelerates on the highway without input from the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine dies while de-accelerating
the engine stalls when letting off the gas pedal
the vehicle will not start or has difficulty starting
the engine makes unusual sounds
such as a high-pressure air or fluid sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, become stuck in gear, or suddenly accelerate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission "lets go" and the engine revs
the transmission will no longer shift and remains stuck in gear
sudden acceleration from the transmission while driving
the vehicle shuts down in traffic
the vehicle won't move or accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to shut down suddenly, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down in the middle of traffic
the alternator quits working
the vehicle needs to be towed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle rolling away from a parked position can cause accidents or damage to property.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls out of a parking garage and hits an object
the vehicle moves on its own while in park.
